{"lemma":"صادُ","slug":"صادُ","root":"#.#.#","root_slug":"_-_-_","root_link":"/words/roots/_-_-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun_prop","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n23908","n24060","n25167","n25310"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B5%D8%A7%D8%AF%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to catch, to capture, to entrap"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to hunt, to chase (game, fish), to fowl, to fish"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"Name of the fourteenth letter of the Arabic alphabet (ص (ṣ)), representing the sound /sˤ/"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare Hebrew צָד (tsad, “to hunt”) and Ugaritic 𐎕𐎄 (ṣd, “to hunt”).\n\nInterrelated with the root ص ي د (ṣ y d), Borrowed from Nabataean Aramaic and ultimately from Proto-Semitic *ṣVd- (“to take food, to capture game, to fish; hunting and gathering”), with early alphabetic symbols interpreted as depicting, a plant, a fishing hook or hunting barb, and in Arabian scripts possibly even a stick-figure human crouched in ambush."},"ipa":["/sˤaː.da/","/sˤaːd/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n23908","headword_ar":"صَادٌّ","root":"Sd","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Turning away, avoiding, shunning,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leaving;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"averse:"},{"kind":"text","text":"fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAd~apN","text_ar":"صَادَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": pl. of both"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sud~aAdN","text_ar":"صُدَّادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and of the fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SawaAd~u","text_ar":"صَوَادُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also. (M.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n24060","headword_ar":"صَادٍ","root":"SdY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(fem. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", and pl. of the latter"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SawaAdK","text_ar":"صَوَادٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"): see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SadK","text_ar":"صَدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  As pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAdiyapN","text_ar":"صَادِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SawaAdK","text_ar":"صَوَادٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies [also]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Tall"},{"kind":"text","text":"palm-trees: (S, K:) and sometimes,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as drink not water:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or palm-trees"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that drink water:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[thus in a copy of the M:] and some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as are tall"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof, and of other trees. (M.)"}],"source_refs":["M","S","K"]},{"entry_id":"n25167","headword_ar":"صَادٌ","root":"Swd","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The name of one of the letters of the alphabet."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L. [See art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"S","text_ar":"ص"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b2-  [It is also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The title of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suwrap","text_ar":"سُورَة"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the thirty-eighth chapter of the Kur-án."},{"kind":"text","text":"] If you make it a sign of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"swrp","text_ar":"سورة"},{"kind":"text","text":", you write it as a single letter, and make it indeclinable with its last letter quiescent [in pronunciation]: if you make it a name for the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"swrp","text_ar":"سورة"},{"kind":"text","text":", you write it as [it is pronounced] in spelling; and say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAdi","text_ar":"صَادِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr, because of the concurrence of two quiescent letters [in the former case]; and you may say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAda","text_ar":"صَادَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", because this is easier of pronunciation: some make it imperfectly decl., considering it as fem. [and a proper name]: and some make it perfectly decl., considering it as masc.; and say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaraA^otu SaAdFA","text_ar":"قَرَاْتُ صَادًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I read,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"recited,"},{"kind":"text","text":"the chapter"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"S","text_ar":"ص"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and the like is done in the cases of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"q","text_ar":"ق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the title of the fiftieth chapter] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n","text_ar":"ن"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the title of the sixtyeighth chapter]. (Msb.) ―         -b3-  Accord. to ISd, its medial radical letter is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L:) accord. to IJ, it is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (MF.)       -A2-  See also art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Syd","text_ar":"صيد"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["L"]},{"entry_id":"n25310","headword_ar":"صَادٌ","root":"Syd","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain vein"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between the eyes of a camel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between the eye and the nose;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whence the disease termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sayad","text_ar":"صَيَد"},{"kind":"text","text":": pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSoyaAdN","text_ar":"اَصْيَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and pl. pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSaAyidu","text_ar":"اَصَايِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSAy^idu","text_ar":"اَصايِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SayadN","text_ar":"صَيَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places. ―         -b3-  And see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSoyadu","text_ar":"اَصْيَدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", likewise in two places.       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Brass;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuforN","text_ar":"صُفْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1753},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"copper:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a species thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cooking-pots made of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sufor","text_ar":"صُفْر"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A'Obeyd, TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of copper:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A'Obeyd, M, TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiydaAnN","text_ar":"صِيدَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, TA,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tiyjaAnN","text_ar":"تِيجَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taAjN","text_ar":"تَاجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and some say that ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SayodaAnN","text_ar":"صَيْدَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v., thus written with fet-h to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"S","text_ar":"ص"},{"kind":"text","text":",] signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"copper."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A3-  See also art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Swd","text_ar":"صود"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["M","K","S","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}